Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.02,0:10:45.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Barely made it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.70,0:10:49.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asu! Asu?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:49.60,0:10:51.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She’s not home yet…
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.90,0:10:54.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I wonder if she’s oka{\fsp-1}y{\fsp}. Maybe she’s still at school.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:54.74,0:10:57.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If she’s outside, I hope she found shelter from the rain.{I hope she’s not out in the rain, maybe?}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.68,0:11:04.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I hate thunder!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.44,0:11:10.73,Dialogue-italic,,0,0,0,,{\t(2271,3272,\c&HFFFFFF&\3c&HFFFFFF&\4c&HFFFFFF&)}What if Asu’s also…{orig: What if… Asu is also…?}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.99,0:11:15.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hang in there, Asu.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.49,0:11:17.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your older sister is coming to get you!{perhaps “alright?” or “okay?” for “ne”}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.55,0:11:24.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The lightning—it hit somewhere nearb{\fsp-1}y{\fsp}.{needs split/retime}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.97,0:11:29.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah, I think someone told me that lightning is attracted to umbrellas.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.77,0:11:42.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Onee-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.93,0:11:46.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Onee-chan! Over here! I’m over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.08,0:11:53.81,Dialogue-italic,,0,0,0,,Come to think of it, Asu wasn’t afraid of the thunder at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.58,0:11:58.01,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I’m so pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.15,0:12:06.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That time, I was so scared of the thunder that when I went to get Asu, I almost gave up halfwa{\fsp-1}y{\fsp}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.44,0:12:08.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Toda{\fsp-1}y{\fsp}, too…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.12,0:12:15.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe Asu doesn’t even need a sister like me.{alt: Asu might not need a sister like me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.34,0:12:20.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh m{\fsp-1}y{\fsp}, Asu-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.77,0:12:21.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What’s wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.40,0:12:24.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You’re completely soaked!{and that yukata you’re carrying has unfixable water damage that renders it worthless!}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.16,0:12:27.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What if you catch a cold?{I am marking this for editing but will probably forget to fix it}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.04,0:12:30.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ma’am, this yukata—
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.98,0:12:33.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, this yukata? You like it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.95,0:12:37.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It has the same design as your sister’s.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.40,0:12:39.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The same?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.84,0:12:43.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That’s why she wouldn’t accept anything else.{alt: Kyo-chan wanted this design no matter what.}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.90,0:12:46.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She even went to our warehouse to search for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.08,0:12:49.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She probably spent the whole day looking.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.54,0:12:52.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,250)}The whole day?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.47,0:12:59.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She probably felt bad because you’ve never had a yukata to wea{\fsp-1}r{\fsp}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:01.16,0:13:06.63,Dialogue-italic,,0,0,0,,She went to all that trouble just to find a matching yukata for me?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.39,0:13:08.85,Dialogue-italic,,0,0,0,,For me…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.49,0:13:14.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She was looking forward to wearing matching yukatas and watching the fireworks togethe{\fsp-1}r{\fsp}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.45,0:13:15.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It’s oka{\fsp-1}y{\fsp}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.96,0:13:18.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It’s just drizzling, so it’ll stop soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.74,0:13:20.45,Dialogue-italic,,0,0,0,,Rain…
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.39,0:13:22.54,Dialogue-italic,,0,0,0,,Just like before.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.78,0:13:26.62,Dialogue-italic,,0,0,0,,The day I forgot my umbrella.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.53,0:13:33.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, more lightning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.66,0:13:35.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Aww, this is inconvenient.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.86,0:13:37.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I’ll get home late.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.64,0:13:41.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Onee-chan?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.09,0:13:45.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Onee-chan! Over here! I’m right over here!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.12,0:13:50.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Onee-chan, you came to pick me up?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.59,0:13:54.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it looks like the rain has stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.69,0:14:00.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You didn’t even use your umbrella, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.01,0:14:07.20,Dialogue-italic,,0,0,0,,Onee-chan hates thunde{\fsp-1}r{\fsp}, but she braved it to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.88,0:14:12.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Since you brought them, let’s use them anywa{\fsp-1}y{\fsp}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.05,0:14:14.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? That’s embarrassing!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.97,0:14:19.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All that and yet…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.35,0:14:21.04,Dialogue-italic,,0,0,0,,Onee-chan, you idiot!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.11,0:14:25.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I… keep causing trouble for my siste{\fsp-1}r{\fsp}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.24,0:14:30.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Kyou is always looking out for you, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.27,0:14:31.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I told her she was stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.54,0:14:36.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all she’s done for me, I called her an idiot.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.11,0:14:38.07,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I…
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.62,0:14:43.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It’s all right, Asu.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.25,0:14:46.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I’m not sure what happened,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.75,0:14:50.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,but your sister worked hard searching for this yukata.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.99,0:14:53.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don’t you wear it and show it to her?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.01,0:14:56.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,O-Onee-chan…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.58,0:15:09.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Onee-chan?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.55,0:15:11.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She’s not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.43,0:15:16.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fireworks…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.33,0:15:26.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asu!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.02,0:15:31.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asu!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.57,0:15:43.13,Dialogue-italic,,0,0,0,,Beautiful!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.44,0:15:46.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Tamaya! Kagiya!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.44,0:15:51.93,notes,,0,0,0,,Tamaya and Kagiya were famous rival fireworks manufacturers. At displays, People would root for their favorite—now, shouting their names is just tradition.{localization: FYUCK YEAR FIERWARKS!!!1}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.94,0:15:51.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Every yea{\fsp-1}r{\fsp}, Asu and I always watch them togethe{\fsp-1}r{\fsp}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.93,0:15:53.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There’s no point if I’m alone.{alt: Watching them alone is meaningless.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.95,0:15:58.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Even so, I expected Asu to be here.{I thought Asu would be here.}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.34,0:15:59.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He{\fsp-1}y{\fsp}, Kyou!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.68,0:16:02.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You came just in time.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.48,0:16:05.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Your special candy apple is almost done.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.40,0:16:06.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Grandpa Yaoichi!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.15,0:16:09.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asu was really looking forward to it.{this is terrible. I want to put something like “…so excited for toay” or something}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.79,0:16:11.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She said she’d come with her siste{\fsp-1}r{\fsp}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.99,0:16:13.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? Asu said that?{Asu? Really? <- this may be a better choice, just for variety}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.61,0:16:14.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.46,0:16:18.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She came to see what stands there were, saying she wanted to escort you around the festival.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.72,0:16:19.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.68,0:16:21.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,She did?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.54,0:16:26.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This memo…
Comment: 0,0:16:26.96,0:16:27.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{so are we gonna set this? w}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.72,0:16:32.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asu… she scouted out a plan so she could escort me around.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.74,0:16:36.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,For me…
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.41,0:16:39.68,Flashback,,0,0,0,,Why did you spend the money by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.41,0:16:42.14,Flashback,,0,0,0,,Who cares about the fireworks festival?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.68,0:16:43.81,Flashback,,0,0,0,,I’m not going!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.28,0:16:48.03,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I’m so stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.25,0:16:51.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.45,0:16:57.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Here, it’s done! Your special candy apple!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.31,0:16:59.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Huh? Kyou-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.57,0:17:05.06,Dialogue-italic,,0,0,0,,Asu wanted to enjoy the festival with me,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.41,0:17:09.21,Dialogue-italic,,0,0,0,,but I didn’t understand her feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.60,0:17:10.92,Dialogue-italic,,0,0,0,,Her feelings.{orig: I threw her feelings away… <- way too long for the spoken line. I concur.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.20,0:17:16.64,Dialogue-italic,,0,0,0,,I promised Mom that I’d take good care of Asu.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.39,0:17:18.62,Dialogue-italic,,0,0,0,,I promised he{\fsp-1}r{\fsp}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.77,0:17:25.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.98,0:17:27.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please let me through.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.68,0:17:30.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Quickl{\fsp-1}y{\fsp}…{it’s entirely fucking unclear whether she’s saying this or just thinking it. The mouth movements could be either mouthbreathing while running or speaking. Even though the words aren’t coming out as though she’s breathing heavily, which lends itself to the theory that she’s thinking, I doubt this show would pay that much attention to detail, and since the mouth movements are non-uniform, I think it can be assumed she is supposedly saying these lines aloud.}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.62,0:17:34.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I have to find Onee-chan quickl{\fsp-1}y{\fsp}, before the fireworks are ove{\fsp-1}r{\fsp}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.01,0:17:36.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Where is she?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.70,0:17:40.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Onee-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.21,0:17:43.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asu?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.17,0:17:46.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asu…
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.28,0:17:48.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asu is here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:59.04,0:18:02.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,600)}Asu!{should be em dash?}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.82,0:18:05.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Onee-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.59,0:18:09.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asu!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.22,0:18:13.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Onee-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.57,0:18:15.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asu!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.72,0:18:18.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Onee-chan…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.79,0:18:32.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Onee-chan, I…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.58,0:18:36.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I… I…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.74,0:18:39.50,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thank you. You wore the yukata.{alt: Thank you for wearing the yukata.}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.67,0:18:42.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Onee-chan…
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.49,0:18:44.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ah, the fireworks!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.13,0:18:50.48,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asu, we were able to watch the fireworks{together} again this yea{\fsp-1.5}{\fsp-1}r{\fsp}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.61,0:18:53.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.17,0:18:56.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We got to see them again this yea{\fsp-1}r{\fsp}.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.12,0:18:57.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.15,0:19:38.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Won’t you rest a little?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:38.75,0:19:42.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Asu! Why are you here? Go home!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.05,0:19:45.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Onee-chan, I want to work too!{WHY DO WE KEEP DOING GODDAMN SHOWS ABOUT CHILD LABOR}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.42,0:19:50.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You don’t have to worry about mone{\fsp-1}y{\fsp}.{orig: You can leave the question of money up to me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.41,0:19:53.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I’ll keep working harder and harde{\fsp-1}r{\fsp}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.36,0:19:54.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It’s all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.61,0:19:56.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I’ll just get another job.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.34,0:19:57.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It’s not that.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.38,0:19:59.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Onee-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.29,0:20:03.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don’t leave me behind.{the gap is too long. It just looked weird lowercase.}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.34,0:20:07.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don’t disappear like Dad did.{daddy would fit better with otou-chan, not otou-san… that said, she is supposed to be 9}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.27,0:20:12.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I called you stupid, but even so…
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.37,0:20:15.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please, don’t leave me!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.36,0:20:22.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oka{\fsp-1}y{\fsp}.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.94,0:20:26.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Onee-chan is right here.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.55,0:20:29.34,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I won’t go anywhere.
Comment: 0,0:20:30.07,0:20:31.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oka{\fsp-1}y{\fsp}.{Alright}{melody completely omits this, idk if we want to do the same or not}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.27,0:20:34.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It’s all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.22,0:20:36.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Onee-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.11,0:20:44.06,Dialogue-italic,,0,0,0,,Asu, it’s oka{\fsp-1}y{\fsp}. Your sister won’t go anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.98,0:20:50.23,Dialogue-italic,,0,0,0,,Kyou, you don’t have to worry about not working hard enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.43,0:21:00.68,Dialogue-italic,,0,0,0,,The only thing I was able to leave behind for you two was a small promise, but it’s protecting you dearl{\fsp-1}y{\fsp}.{while I agree with that… No idea how to reword to make it not retarded}{idea: The only thing I was able to leave behind for you two was a small promise, but it’s protecting you dearly.}
